| Caltagirone, Sergio; Pendergast, Andrew; Betz, Christopher                                                                      | The Diamond Model of Intrusion Analysis                                                                                              | The paper describes the Diamond Model of intrusion analysis, which allows integration of real-time intelligence into intrusion analysis, including the construction of attack threads, clusters and groups. This is useful for identifying and modelling threat actor tactics, techniques and procedures (e.g. MITRE’s ATT&CK framework), similar to the paper’s example of combining the diamond model with the kill chain.                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| Casola, Valentina; De Benedictis, Alessandra; Mazzocca, Carlo; Montanari, Rebecca                                               | Designing Secure and Resilient Cyber-Physical Systems: a Model-based Moving Target Defense Approach                                  | Backgound information and reference.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          |
| Chen, Thomas M.; Sanchez-Aarnoutse, Juan Carlos; Buford, John                                                                   | Petri Net Modeling of Cyber-Physical Attacks on Smart Grid                                                                           | The paper proposes the use of Petri nets to model coordinated cyber-physical attacks on the smart grid. The approach is flexible enough to consider timed and delayed intrusions, or even uncoordinated attacks by multiple threat actors.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    |
| Couretas, Jerry M.                                                                                                              | Taxonomy of Cyber Threats                                                                                                            | Book chapter that provides a good overview of cyber threats and threat models.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
