| Zalewski, Janusz; Drager, Steven; McKeever, William; Kornecki, Andrew J.                                                        | Threat modeling for security assessment in cyberphysical systems                                                                     | The paper presents two important concepts. First, that a security breach in CPS is not a binary event - there is a degraded state and the paper proposes using threat modeling to derive the probabilities of landing in a degraded state in a Markov chain model. Second, that fault tree analysis is broader than attack trees, as it covers failures beyond what the attacker’s action may result in. This sets cyber physical threats apart from traditional STRIDE taxonomy.                                                                                                                                                             |
| Zenitani, Kengo                                                                                                                 | Attack graph analysis: An explanatory guide                                                                                          | The paper provides a detailed explanation of different types of attack graphs, derived metrics and limitations                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
